      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that higher wages boost the local economy is a well-worn, theoretical concept that often rings true in practice. When workers earn more, they spend that extra income on local goods and services, creating a positive feedback loop for businesses. This increased consumer demand can actually help offset some of the higher labor costs you face. Ultimately, a higher wage floor stimulates the local market, which is a net positive for community commerce.",
      "source": "target",
