      "content": "that sounds good in theory i guess, but it feels like you're leaning pretty hard into the \"positive feedback loop\" side of things. what about the downside? i'm seeing plenty of other owners saying they'll have to let people go or cut hours just to keep the lights on. isn't it a bit of a stretch to call it a \"net positive\" when it might actually kill off local shops?",
